<A NAME="profile">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="1" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" VALIGN="TOP">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#000000">
  <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4" CELLSPACING="1" WIDTH="100%">
    <TR BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="MIDDLE">
      <TD COLSPAN="5" ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT CLASS="normal"><STRONG>User Profile</STRONG><BR>There are several Usergroups in SPChat. These can be recognized by the symbol before the username:</FONT></TD>
    </TR>
    <TR BGCOLOR="lightblue" VALIGN="MIDDLE">
      <TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT CLASS="normal"><STRONG>Display</STRONG></FONT></TD>
      <TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT CLASS="normal"><STRONG>Meaning</STRONG></FONT></TD>
    </TR>
    <TR BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal"><img src="modules/SPChat/images/admin1.gif"></FONT></TD>
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal">Users with this symbol are admins. They control the room and are able to ban or kick any user and create new admins for the room. </i></FONT></TD>
    </TR>
    <TR BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal"><img src="modules/SPChat/images/user1.gif"></i></FONT></TD>
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal">These are registered users. They are able to have and maintain a user profile.</i></FONT></TD>
    </TR>
    <TR BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal"><img src="modules/SPChat/images/guest1.gif"></i></FONT></TD>
      <TD ALIGN="left"><FONT class="normal">Guests are shown with this symbol. They usually use different usernames each time they login. It is not possible for guests to create and/or use a profile.</i></FONT></TD>
    </TR>
    <TR BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="MIDDLE">
      <TD COLSPAN="5" ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT CLASS="normal">As admin or registered user you are able to create a personal profile. Simply click on your username and follow the instructions to create and/or modify the profile.</FONT></TD>
    </TR>
  </TABLE>
  </TD></TR>
</TABLE>

